{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0ab84538-18fd-4afb-a6e8-1d786c2bc3ee","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you need to make these changes:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove this line entirely -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is absent or `false`.\n\n2. **Run tests differently** — instead of `dotnet test`, you can now also use:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project YourTest.csproj -- --help   # see new CLI options\n   dotnet test   # still works, but routes through the new platform\n   ```\n\n3. **Update any CI/CLI flags** — some VSTest arguments (e.g., `--logger trx`) change syntax. The new platform equivalents typically use `--report-trx` or similar. Run with `--help` to see available options.\n\n4. **Extensions** — if you use VSTest adapters (e.g., coverage, loggers), check that Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents are referenced. Common ones:\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` (for TRX output)\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` (for coverage)\n\nThat's it — removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is the key change. The SDK handles the rest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2163a49c-f16f-4cc7-b60d-644826393014","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request in their repo.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":448},"id":"0b8ee060-9502-4d60-97a5-5d27984bc169","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:21:21.150Z","parentId":"98c6d370-33d7-4df8-ab6b-f173490dbdc1"}
